{{Infobox person | name = Sarah Gorelick | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1931|10|30}} | known_for = [[Mercury 13]], aviation }}
'''Sarah Ratley (nee Gorelick)''' (born October 30, 1931) is an [[United States|American]] pilot and one of the [[Mercury 13]] female [[Astronaut|astronauts]] group.
== Biography == Born on October 30, 1931 in [[Kansas]], Gorelick learned to fly in 1949 and raced in the [[Powder Puff Derby (1947)|Powder Puff Derby]] and toured with the [[Ninety-Nines]]. She graduated from the [[University of Denver]] with a Bachelors of Science in Mathematics, minoring in physics, chemistry and aeronautics, then worked as an engineer at [[AT&T]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astronautix.com/g/gorelick.html |publisher=Astronautix |title=Gorelick, Sarah Lee nee Ratley |accessdate=14 June 2018}}</ref><ref name="nasm">{{cite web|url=https://airandspace.si.edu/support/wall-of-honor/sarah-lee-gorelick-ratley|title=Sarah Lee Gorelick Ratley|publisher=National Air and Space Museum|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref>
During a tour of Europe she heard about a space research program, which produced the [[Mercury 13]] and was invited to take part upon her return.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CBC|title=The Mercury 13: The women who trained for space flight until NASA shut them down |url=http://www.cbc.ca/radio/day6/episode-388-trump-s-mob-ties-new-brunswick-flood-muterkelly-p-k-subban-s-dad-mercury-13-and-more-1.4646381/the-mercury-13-the-women-who-trained-for-space-flight-until-nasa-shut-them-down-1.4646407|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref> She underwent invasive testing, including freezing the inner ear with ice water to induce vertigo. She said of the experience, "The tests didn’t bother me at all…. When you are young you can take anything. My mind was made up: I was going to pass."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://magazine.du.edu/alumni/a-woman-with-wings/ |title=A woman with wings |accessdate=15 June 2018|date=1 September 2007 |author=Nicole Branan |publisher=University of Denver Magazine}}</ref>
After Mercury 13, Gorelick became an accountant with the [[Internal Revenue Service]] and in 2007 received an honorary Doctorate of Science from the [[University of Wisconsin]].<ref name="nasm" />
