{{Vietnamese name|Võ|Vo|Thanh Tùng}}
'''Võ Thanh Tùng''' (born 26 July 1985) is a Vietnamese Paralympic swimmer.<ref>[http://www.baomoi.com/Vo-Thanh-Tung-doat-HCV-boi-loi/55/5376234.epi Võ Thanh Tùng đoạt HCV bơi lội]</ref><ref>[http://www.baomoi.com/Van-%C4%91ong-vien-khuyet-tat-Vo-Thanh-Tung/55/5561207.epi Vận động viên khuyết tật Võ Thanh Tùng]</ref> He won gold in the men's 50m freestyle S5 at the [[2010 Asian Para Games]] in China.<ref>[http://ipc.infostradasports.com/asp/lib/TheASP.asp?pageid=8937&sportid=514&personid=965881 IPC bio]</ref> He is seen as a possible medal contender for his nation.<ref>[http://vietnamnews.vnagency.com.vn/Sports/229342/national-team-aims-for-one-medal-at-least.html Viet Nam News]</ref> He lives in [[Cần Thơ]] and had [[poliomyelitis]] as a child.<ref>[http://www.nhandan.com.vn/cmlink/nhandan-online/homepage/sports/personalities/disabled-swimmer-vo-thanh-tung-1.283993 Nhân Dân Online Võ Thanh Tùng]</ref>

